def: In the manner of a conspirator; by conspiracy. Milton.
A genus of large arenaceous fossil Foraminifera found in theCretaceous rocks. The species are globular, or nearly so, and are ofall sizes up to that of a tennis ball.
A colonnade or covered ambulatory, especially in classicalstyles of architecture; usually, a colonnade at the entrance of abuilding.
To befall. [Poetic]I wish all good befortune you. Shak.
Imparting strength or tone; strengthening; invigorating; as, abracing north wind.
One of the free-swimming sexual zooids of Siphonophora.
In a univocal manner; in one term; in one sense; notequivocally.How is sin univocally distinguished into venial and mortal, if thevenial be not sin Bp. Hall.
Chips made by one who whittles; shavings cut from a stick witha knife.

In Ireland, a lord or proprietor of a tract of land or of acastle, elected by a family, under the system of tanistry.This family [the O'Hanlons] were tanists of a large territory withinthe present county of Armagh. M. A. Lower.
